snippet.textDisplay: Salman Ahmad knocked it, killed it & bamboozled with the genius idea to collaborate with Brian O'Connell (his school friend) & introduce Sufi Rock which took the entire subcontinent by storm.. since Junoon's Inception back in early 90's their main USP was fusion of classical instrument with American style Electric guitar, bass guitar & more importantly the Lyrics which had Sufi essence. Sufism has that power to reach the soul & bring more closer to the Almighty Creator. Saein, Muk Gaye ne, Ilteja, Bheegi yaadein are my personal favorite..
